<li><a href="https://gionkunz.github.io/chartist-js/">Chartist</a> - Simple, lightweight chart library that uses SVG to render the chart, and CSS to style it.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/ecomfe/echarts">ECharts</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/ecomfe/echarts" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">46.3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":46318,"repo":"ecomfe/echarts"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - A powerful charting and visualization library for browser.</li>
<li><a href="http://c3js.org/">C3.js</a> - D3 based reusable chart library.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js">Plotly</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">13.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":13174,"repo":"plotly/plotly.js"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Built on top of d3 and stack.gl, allowing users to create basic charts and SVG maps.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/jacomyal/sigma.js">sigma.js</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/jacomyal/sigma.js" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">9.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":9382,"repo":"jacomyal/sigma.js"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Graphs / Network diagram library built with canvas.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.taucharts.com/">TauCharts</a> - Unique syntax that lets the developer describe the data using DSL. Has the ability to create facets.</li>
<li><a href="https://dc-js.github.io/dc.js/">dc.js</a> - D3 Library with <a href="http://square.github.io/crossfilter/">crossfilter</a> support</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/zingchart/awesome-charting/week/#2016-9</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/zingchart/awesome-charting/week/#2016-9</guid><pubDate>Mon, 29 Feb 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[zingchart/awesome-charting Feb 15th - Feb 21st, 2016]]></title><description><![CDATA[<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>
<li><a href="http://www.rgraph.net/">rgraph</a> - 2D/3D javascript charts with google sheets import capabilites.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.chartjs.org/">Chart.js</a> - Tiny library (11kb!) including core chart types.</li>
<li><a href="https://d3js.org/">D3.js</a> - Allows the user to manipulate documents based on data to render charts in SVG.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/danvk/dygraphs">dygraphs</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/danvk/dygraphs" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">2.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":2912,"repo":"danvk/dygraphs"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Interactive zoomable time series charts.</li>
<li><a href="https://github.com/palantir/plottable">Plottable</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/palantir/plottable" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">2.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":2771,"repo":"palantir/plottable"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Library with OOP style syntax to build charts.</li>
<h2>Free Libraries</h2>
<li><a href="https://developers.google.com/chart/">Google Charts</a> - Maps are dialed in (of course) and some cool animation options. Extensive docs and use community (forum).</li>
<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>Angular</h3>
<li><a href="https://github.com/n3-charts/line-chart">n3-charts</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/n3-charts/line-chart" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">1.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":1209,"repo":"n3-charts/line-chart"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Easy to use library written with AngularJS, rendering charts with D3.</li>
<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>Ember</h3>
<li><a href="http://addepar.github.io/ember-charts/#/overview">Ember Charts</a> - Five basic chart types ready to go in Ember.js projects.</li>
<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>jQuery</h3>
<li><a href="http://www.flotcharts.org/">Flot</a> - A JavaScript charting library for jQuery. Contains useful chart types but looks like it may no longer be in active development.</li>
<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>React</h3>
<li><a href="https://github.com/esbullington/react-d3">react-d3</a><a data-role="trackawesomelist-badge" href="https://github.com/esbullington/react-d3" style="text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;"><span style="color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;"><span style="padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;">stars</span><span style="padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;">1.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{"type":"repo","stargazerCount":1768,"repo":"esbullington/react-d3"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Charting library that relies on React for generating SVG markup and d3 to calculate path values.</li>
<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>
<li><a href="http://datavizcatalogue.com">Dataviz Catalogue</a> - A place to go when you're wondering which chart type is best. A project by Severino Ribecca.</li>
<li><a href="http://stephanieevergreen.com">Evergreen Data</a> - Information and opinions on presenting data more effectively.</li>
<li><a href="http://flowingdata.com">Flowing Data</a> - A resource on maps, visualizations, stats, and design by Nathan Yau, formerly of the New York Times.</li>
<li><a href="http://junkcharts.typepad.com">Junk Charts</a> - Dataviz critic (and Columbia professor) Kaiser Fung breaks down data visualizations to identify what is wrong and recommends ways to make them better.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.visualisingdata.com">Visualizing Data</a> - Dataviz consultant Andy Kirk compiles examples, resources, and reference materials on the subject of charting and visualization.</li>
<li><a href="http://well-formed-data.net/archives/1210/little-boxes">Well Formed Data</a> - Thought pieces on information visualization and design by Moritz Stefaner previously of the World Economic Forum.</li>
]]></description><link>https://www.trackawesomelist.com/zingchart/awesome-charting/week/#2016-7</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.trackawesomelist.com/zingchart/awesome-charting/week/#2016-7</guid><pubDate>Mon, 15 Feb 2016 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>